This paper belongs to the field of social media and its adoption and use by nonprofit organizations. The paper discusses the factors that drive the adoption and use of social media by nonprofit organizations, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also uses data analysis and modeling techniques to examine the determinants of social media utilization, which falls under the categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI) and social computing (cs.SOC). Additionally, the paper discusses the governance and strategy aspects of social media utilization, which falls under the categories of computer and society (cs.CC) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
